5 §1956. Definitions
6 For purposes of this Chapter, the following terms shall have the
7 meanings unless the context indicated otherwise:
8 (1) "Voter assistance provider" means any individual or entity providing
9 nonpartisan assistance to voters for registration, absentee ballot applications,
10 or voting procedures.
11 (2) "Voting rights violations" means actions that unlawfully discourage
12 or prohibit a person from registering or voting, including intimidation,
13 misinformation, or discriminatory practices.
14 §1957. Protection against voter intimidation and misinformation
15 A. Prohibition on intimidation and misinformation.
16 (1) No person shall knowingly or intentionally intimidate, deceive,
17 misinform, or coerce any voter, prospective voter, or voter assistance provider
18 regarding any aspect of registration, voting, or qualifications to vote.
19 (a) Prohibited conduct includes but is not limited to threatening
20 language, dissemination of false information regarding voter eligibility, voting
21 requirements, polling times, or locations.
22 (b) This Subsection reinforces existing protections against intimidation
23 under R.S. 18:1461.4 and complements laws governing conduct at polling
24 places.
25 B. Enforcement and penalties.
26 (1) Violations of this Section shall be a misdemeanor, punishable by a
27 fine of not less than one thousand dollars and not more than five thousand
28 dollars, imprisonment for up to six months, or both.
29 (2) Violations involving organized or systematic voter suppression shall
